      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you're feeling a heavy weight of existential dread, which is a very common human experience, though it can feel incredibly isolating. That feeling that \"nothing actually matters\" is a philosophical concept known as nihilism, and while it can be paralyzing, many people find that acknowledging the raw mechanics of the universe actually frees them to appreciate the small, fleeting moments of beauty within it. You don't have to believe in magic or a grand cosmic plan to find meaning; sometimes, meaning is just found in the act of surviving the darkness itself.\n\nI hear you, and I want to remind you that even in the deepest darkest tunnels, there are often tiny, unexpected things happening that you might not notice right now. If you're feeling this way, please consider reaching out to a trusted friend or a mental health professional who can help you navigate these feelings. You are not alone in this struggle, and there are people who care about your well-being and want to help you find a path forward.",
